  "20,000 kcal/m2/year": "",
  "NPP equals GPP minus plant respiration (NPP = 20,000 - 12,000 = 8,000 kcal/m2/year). This 8,000 kcal represents the energy stored as plant biomass and available to herbivores.": "",
  "In an ocean ecosystem, phytoplankton capture 50,000 kcal of energy. Using the 10% rule, how much energy would be available to a tertiary consumer (such as a tuna eating smaller fish)?": "",
